Ask HN: What techs are limited only by amount of energy humanity produces?
text:
I guess this is the most appropriate place on the internet to ask this kind of question.

What technologies that are impossible right now that would be possible if humanity doubles the amount of electric energy produced? How about 10x, 100x?

Suppose we 100x it, what's the next biggest bottleneck?

Deceptive Co-founder: Do I have a right to any equity/cash reimbursement?
text:
I recently discovered that my cofounder has been hiding things from me as we prepare to raise. When we started working together, it was agreed that we would both own half of the business, with decision making tie-break going to them. We drafted a document, which was never signed (I know, stupid... I thought I could trust them). My co-founder had already incorporated the business under their own name before we started working together, so I don't have any signed documents stating my ownership of the company.

Since then, we have both been working hard and both investing our own money into the business. Now that we're close to raising, we are parting ways. Do I have any right to equity or recuperation of my costs?

I could make things really ugly, but prefer to part ways as amicably as possible.

Thanks!
